epend on AI output.","test_description":"Candidate Integration (chosen): create one client/account quota bucket with limit K, launch M concurrent call() operations via stub transport, assert aggregate admitted attempts respect shared bucket rather than per-caller independent limits; catches bugs where each caller gets isolated counters. Adjacent Unit candidate: test bucket decrement function in isolation; catches arithmetic bugs but misses wiring where callers accidentally use different bucket instances. Rejected System because behavior explicitly scopes to same-process shared state, not real network effects.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When multiple requests are waiting to be sent, they are dispatched in the order they were originally submitted.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Ordering bugs arise in queue + scheduler + dispatcher interaction under async contention. A pure unit test of queue data structure may miss integration issues in dispatch timing/handoff.","test_description":"Candidate Integration (chosen): enqueue several blocked requests through client under quota pressure, then release capacity stepwise via stub transport/fake clock; assert dispatch order matches submission order IDs; catches race conditions where dispatcher reorders tasks. Adjacent Unit candidate: test FIFO queue class pop order; catches data-structure defects only, not async integration reorder bugs. Rejected System because real OS/network scheduling is not required to reproduce this in-process ordering failure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]}
